{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3888ebfd-4788-4b8f-b958-141b5d3e33b3","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your crash dump. The `dump-collect` skill I have available is only for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them — so let me give you direct guidance instead.\n\n### Analyzing a .NET crash dump\n\n**Option 1: `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform)\n```bash\n# Install if needed\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n\n# Analyze\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\n\nUseful commands inside the interactive session:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrthreads` | List managed threads |\n| `pe` | Print last exception on current thread |\n| `clrstack` | Show managed call stack |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary |\n| `setthread <id>` | Switch to a specific thread |\n\nStart with `pe` — it will usually show you the unhandled exception and stack trace that caused the crash.\n\n**Option 2: Visual Studio** (Windows)\n- Open the `.dmp` file directly in VS → click **\"Debug with Managed Only\"** for a visual experience.\n\n**Option 3: `lldb` + SOS** (Linux/macOS)\n```bash\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\nplugin load libsosplugin.so\nsos PrintException\nsos ClrStack\n```\n\nWould you like me to walk you through any of these in more detail?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"239dd576-22ff-4e17-9a81-ba5cdaee3a25","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description says it's for configuring and collecting crash dumps, and explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo the dump-collect skill is not appropriate here. I should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their dump file.","outputTokens":458,"requestId":"2C4E:15C54:1444B7A:171D4A6:69F94F26"},"id":"750870ed-e894-411c-9b81-474909787e8c","timestamp":"2026-05-